  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Poonam versus Dule Singh & Ors.  pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_12_1_23','2025INSC1284'); ><font size='4'> <strong>POONAM<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>DULE SINGH & ORS.  </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 12 S.C.R. 1</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1284</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006562025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup></strong><br> Issue for Consideration The High Court upheld the judgment of the trial Court by recording a finding that by failing to disclose conviction in the affidavit filed along with nomination form, there was a breach of Rule 24-A of the Madhya Pradesh Nagar Palika Nirvachan Niyam, 1994 and was rightly set aside. Headnotes&dagger; Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 &ndash; s.138 &ndash; Madhya Pradesh Municipalities Act, 1961 &ndash; s.22(1)(d)(iii) &ndash; Madhya Pradesh Nagar Palika Nirvachan Niyam, 1994 &ndash; Petitioner suffered a conviction u/s.138 of the Negotiable Instruments<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 06-11-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CIVIL) No. 12000/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_12_1_23','2025INSC1284','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-s